ce:section.ce:para:
The fabricated dual-responsive immunoassay using the Ab2-CdSe NCs-PAMAM-CNTs conjugate as the amplification label, together with the CER amplification method, was employed for quantification of CEA with different concentrations. For the fluorescence assay, the targeting CEA was detected by using Cd2+ to trigger the weakly fluorescent Rhod-5N to produce strong fluorescence. As seen in Fig. 3
                         A and B, the fluorescence intensity increases with increasing the concentration of CEA in a linear range from 1.0 pg/mL to 20 ng/mL with the regression equation of y = 223758 lg (x) + 64585.0 (R2 = 0.990). The LOD was calculated to be 0.25 pg/mL at 3 times the standard deviation of the blank measurements (S/N = 3). For the electrochemistry assay, the SWV peaks (Fig. 3C, D) at −0.73 V also increase with increasing the concentration of CEA and displayed a good linear relationship inthe range from 5.0 pg/mL to 50 ng/mL. The regression equation was expressed as y = 11.273 lg (x) - 5.1370 (R2 = 0.981) with the LOD of 1.7 pg/mL according the S/N = 3. In short, the developed immunosensor performed a wider linear range from 1 pg/mL to 50 ng/mL with a lower detection limit of 0.25 pg/mL compared with previous reports (Table 1
                        ). The possible reasons of the high sensitivity may be due to the combination effects of the cation-exchange reaction that releases a huge amount of Cd2+ and the large specific surface area of the CNTs and PAMAM that could bind more CdSe NCs to significantly increase the signals. In addition, both FL and EC detection range were from 5.0 pg/mL to 20 ng/mL in the dual-responsive detection, which could meet the requirement of clinical detection with the normal range of CEA in human as 2.5–5 ng/mL [37]. The self-correcting ability refers to the ability to identify false positive signals, that is, two methods are used to determine the same sample, if the two results are consistent, the method is proved accurate. If there is a discrepancy between the two outputs, it indicates that we need to compare them with the standard method. Here, these dual signal outputs show a good agreement (Fig. S7A, R2 = 0.9904) between the methods, which displays an attractive self-correcting ability that is capable of avoiding false positive signal and making the detection result more reliable.
